  "doc_id": "4062",
  "text": "Height-for-age measurements were plotted together with the published 50th percentile reference curve for untreated rapidly or slowly progressing MPS VI patients [CITATION_1] . Height Z-scores were generated separately for the group of patients with high uGAG levels and those with low uGAG and were based on the corresponding MPS VI reference population growth chart. Mean Z-score change from first available pretreatment assessment to last follow-up was calculated with and without stratification by age at treatment initiation (0-3, N3-6, N6-9, N9-12, N12-15, and N15-18 years). P-values for the change in Z-score were derived from paired 2-sided t-tests. A Pearson correlation coefficient was calculated to assess the relationship between age at treatment initiation and change in Z-score.",
